  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Transfer your<strong> BBQ pulled pork</strong> to an<strong> oven-proof dish</strong>,<strong> </strong>draining away half<strong> </strong>of the juices</p><p>Top with your <strong>gochujang paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and a 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong>, then cover with <strong>tin foil </strong>and put the dish in the oven for an initial 20 min</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1656238123230-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1656238123230-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1656238123230-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1656238123230-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1656238123230-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces and add to a baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Drizzle with your <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, give everything a good mix up, then put the tray[s] in the oven for 25-30 min or until the potatoes are crisp and cooked through</p><p>Once cooked, sprinkle over your <strong>black sesame seeds</strong> – these are your <strong>sesame roasted potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1656238127953-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1656238127953-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1656238127953-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1656238127953-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1656238127953-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Bash your <strong>cucumber</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> and chop it into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Tip: Bash the cucumber in it’s bag. By bruising the cucumber, the water is drawn out more easily!</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-2-1726061034285-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-2-1726061034285-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-2-1726061034285-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
